---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const RELEASES = 'https://github.com/michaelbeijer/superlookup-desktop/releases/latest';
---

<Base
	title="SuperLookup — a translator’s reference web in one window"
	description="A free desktop app that opens every terminology and reference site — Superterm, IATE, Linguee, ProZ, Glosbe, Wikipedia and 35+ more — each in its own ad-free tab, summoned by a global hotkey on whatever term you’ve selected. Windows, macOS & Linux."
>
	<div class="lander">
		<section class="lander-hero">
			<div class="lander-hero-copy">
				<h1>Your reference web, in one window.</h1>
				<p class="lead">
					SuperLookup opens every terminology and reference site a translator
					reaches for — each in its own ad-free tab — and jumps to the front
					searching whatever term you’ve selected, from <em>any</em> app.
				</p>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="btn-primary" href={RELEASES} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download free ↓</a>
					<a class="btn-ghost" href="https://supervertaler.com" rel="noopener">Or inside Supervertaler →</a>
				</div>
				<p class="platforms">Windows · macOS · Linux — no install, no account, no sign-up.</p>
			</div>

			<figure class="app-shot">
				<div class="mock" role="img" aria-label="The SuperLookup desktop app: a search bar over a row of browser tabs, one per reference site, showing a result.">
					<div class="mock-bar">
						<span class="mock-dot r"></span><span class="mock-dot y"></span><span class="mock-dot g"></span>
						<span class="mock-title">SuperLookup</span>
					</div>
					<div class="mock-controls">
						<span class="mock-sel">Dutch</span>
						<span class="mock-swap">⇄</span>
						<span class="mock-sel">English</span>
						<span class="mock-q">octrooi</span>
						<span class="mock-go">Search</span>
					</div>
					<div class="mock-tabs">
						<span class="mtab active">📚 Superterm</span>
						<span class="mtab">🇪🇺 IATE</span>
						<span class="mtab">📗 Linguee</span>
						<span class="mtab">📘 Glosbe</span>
						<span class="mtab">📖 Wikipedia</span>
						<span class="mtab more">+34</span>
					</div>
					<div class="mock-page">
						<div class="mock-sense">
							<div class="mock-lbl">Intellectual property · noun</div>
							<div class="mock-terms">patent</div>
							<div class="mock-meta">octrooi → patent <span class="mock-src">Superterm</span></div>
						</div>
						<div class="mock-sense">
							<div class="mock-lbl">Law · noun</div>
							<div class="mock-terms">letters patent</div>
							<div class="mock-meta">octrooi → letters patent <span class="mock-src">IATE</span></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</figure>
		</section>

		<section class="how">
			<h2>How it works</h2>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Select a term</strong> anywhere — your CAT tool, a PDF, an email, a browser.</li>
				<li><strong>Press the global hotkey</strong> (default <code>Ctrl+Alt+L</code>). SuperLookup jumps to the front, already searching it.</li>
				<li><strong>Flick through the tabs</strong> — every site opens in its own embedded, ad-free view, with your login remembered and trackers blocked.</li>
			</ol>
		</section>

		<section class="features">
			<h2>Why a desktop app</h2>
			<div class="feature-grid">
				<div class="feature">
					<h3><span class="fic">⌨️</span> Global hotkey</h3>
					<p>Summon it on any selected text, from any application — no copy-paste, no alt-tabbing.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="feature">
					<h3><span class="fic">🗂️</span> 40+ resources, one place</h3>
					<p>Superterm, IATE, Linguee, ProZ, Glosbe, bab.la, Wikipedia, EUR-Lex, medical &amp; EU terminology and more — enable only what you use.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="feature">
					<h3><span class="fic">🚫</span> Ad-free &amp; private</h3>
					<p>An EasyList-based blocker strips ads and trackers from every tab, so the sites are cleaner than in a normal browser.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="feature">
					<h3><span class="fic">🔐</span> Logins that stick</h3>
					<p>Sign into ProZ, Juremy or Superterm once and stay signed in across launches.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="feature">
					<h3><span class="fic">🔎</span> Inline previews</h3>
					<p>Wikipedia, Wiktionary and Wikidata list their matching pages right inside the tab; site favicons and adjustable zoom keep it tidy.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="feature">
					<h3><span class="fic">🪶</span> Light &amp; self-contained</h3>
					<p>A single download that runs without installing anything, and lives in the system tray so the hotkey works even when the window is closed.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="download">
			<h2>Download</h2>
			<div class="dl-row">
				<a class="dl-pill" href={RELEASES} target="_blank" rel="noopener">🪟 Windows</a>
				<a class="dl-pill" href={RELEASES} target="_blank" rel="noopener">🍎 macOS</a>
				<a class="dl-pill" href={RELEASES} target="_blank" rel="noopener">🐧 Linux</a>
			</div>
			<p class="dl-note">
				Each build is self-contained (~150–210 MB) and starts in a couple of
				seconds. New to it? Read the <a href="/help">quick help</a>. SuperLookup
				also comes built into the
				<a href="https://supervertaler.com" rel="noopener">Supervertaler Workbench</a>,
				alongside your own termbases and translation memories.
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</Base>
